<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1091" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1091">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/302.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Governor of Florida</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tallahassee, Fla.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-27">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 27, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Citizens of Florida now in Mexico City have to-day wired me requesting
                            that I ascertain immediately whether United States will intervene Mexico
                            and give them warning. Such information as you can consistently furnish
                            me will be appreciated for this purpose.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Albert W. Gilchrist.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>